Description: Uses the 'PLINK 2' pgenlib library and its native importers
    (<https://github.com/chrchang/plink-ng>) to ingest PGEN, PLINK 1 BED,
    PED/MAP, TPED/TFAM, VCF/BCF, BGEN, Oxford GEN, HAPS/legend, EIGENSTRAT,
    and legacy dosage sources into bounded, file-backed 'Rfmalloc' layouts.
    Hardcalls, dosages, and phase are transferred as typed record panels,
    allowing the destination to choose a packed codec or full-precision
    storage without constructing a complete R matrix. The vendored native
    readers are also exposed through 'R_RegisterCCallable' for sibling
    packages.
